Joe Aribo has rejected a new offer of 7,000 pounds a week from Rangers. The Super Eagles midfielder has a year left on his contract with the Glasgow club. He said the offer is not good enough. It comes at a time when the versatile midfielder has been linked with several Premier League clubs including Aston Villa and Crystal Palace. Some reports have even suggested that Rangersâ€™ bitter city rivals Celtic could try to snatch Aribo by doubling what is now on the table.